msgctxt "mn123:18.1"
msgid "Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "I have learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

#. VAR: udena → uddena (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: visado → visuddho (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn123:18.2"
msgid "‘yadā, ānanda, bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, visadova nikkhamati amakkhito udena amakkhito semhena amakkhito ruhirena amakkhito kenaci asucinā suddho visado. "
msgstr "‘When the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, he emerges already clean, unsoiled by waters, mucus, blood, or any other kind of impurity, pure and clean. "

msgctxt "mn123:18.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, maṇiratanaṃ kāsike vatthe nikkhittaṃ neva maṇiratanaṃ kāsikaṃ vatthaṃ makkheti nāpi kāsikaṃ vatthaṃ maṇiratanaṃ makkheti. "
msgstr "Suppose a jewel-treasure was placed on a cloth from Kāsī. The jewel would not soil the cloth, nor would the cloth soil the jewel. "

msgctxt "mn123:18.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn123:18.5"
msgid "Ubhinnaṃ suddhattā. "
msgstr "Because of the cleanliness of them both. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn123:18.6"
msgid "Evameva kho, ānanda, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, visadova nikkhamati amakkhito udena amakkhito semhena amakkhito ruhirena amakkhito kenaci asucinā suddho visado’ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, he emerges already clean, unsoiled by waters, mucus, blood, or any other kind of impurity, pure and clean.’ "

msgctxt "mn123:18.7"
msgid "Yampi, bhante … pe … idampāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato acchariyaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ dhāremi. (16) "
msgstr "This too I remember as an incredible quality of the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, sc20
msgctxt "mn123:19.1"
msgid "Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "I have learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

msgctxt "mn123:19.2"
msgid "‘yadā, ānanda, bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, dve udakassa dhārā antalikkhā pātubhavanti—ekā sītassa, ekā uṇhassa; yena bodhisattassa udakakiccaṃ karonti mātu cā’ti. "
msgstr "‘When the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, two streams of water appear in the sky, one cool, one warm, for bathing the being intent on awakening and his mother.’ "

msgctxt "mn123:19.3"
msgid "Yampi, bhante … pe … idampāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato acchariyaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ dhāremi. (17) "
msgstr "This too I remember as an incredible quality of the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya20, sc21
msgctxt "mn123:20.1"
msgid "Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "I have learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

# NOTE: SN 47.12 and SN 52.9 make it clear that asabhi does not refer to the sound of the speech, but to it’s dramatic and imposing nature.
msgctxt "mn123:20.2"
msgid "‘sampatijāto, ānanda, bodhisatto samehi pādehi pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhahitvā uttarābhimukho sattapadavītihārena gacchati, setamhi chatte anudhāriyamāne, sabbā ca disā viloketi, āsabhiñca vācaṃ bhāsati—aggohamasmi lokassa, jeṭṭhohamasmi lokassa, seṭṭhohamasmi lokassa. Ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’ti. "
msgstr "‘As soon as he’s born, the being intent on awakening stands firm with his own feet on the ground. Facing north, he takes seven strides with a white parasol held above him, surveys all quarters, and makes this dramatic statement: “I am the foremost in the world! I am the eldest in the world! I am the best in the world! This is my last rebirth. Now there are no more future lives.”’ "

msgctxt "mn123:20.3"
msgid "Yampi, bhante … pe … idampāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato acchariyaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ dhāremi. (18) "
msgstr "This too I remember as an incredible quality of the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya21, pts-vp-pli3.124, sc22
msgctxt "mn123:21.1"
msgid "Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "I have learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

msgctxt "mn123:21.2"
msgid "‘yadā, ānanda, bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, atha sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso loke pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ. "
msgstr "‘When the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, then—in this world with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods. "

msgctxt "mn123:21.3"
msgid "Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā yatthapime candimasūriyā evaṃmahiddhikā evaṃmahānubhāvā ābhāya nānubhonti tatthapi appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso loke pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ. "
msgstr "Even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space—so utterly dark that even the light of the moon and the sun, so mighty and powerful, makes no impression—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods. "

msgctxt "mn123:21.4"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti—aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannāti. "
msgstr "And the sentient beings reborn there recognize each other by that light: “So, it seems other sentient beings have been reborn here!” "

msgctxt "mn123:21.5"
msgid "Ayañca dasasahassī lokadhātu saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati, appamāṇo ca uḷāro obhāso loke pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvan’ti. "
msgstr "And this galaxy shakes and rocks and trembles. And an immeasurable, magnificent light appears in the world, surpassing the glory of the gods.’ "

msgctxt "mn123:21.6"
msgid "Yampi, bhante … pe … idampāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato acchariyaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ dhāremī”ti. (19) "
msgstr "This too I remember as an incredible and amazing quality of the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya22, sc23
msgctxt "mn123:22.1"
msgid "“Tasmātiha tvaṃ, ānanda, idampi tathāgatassa acchariyaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ dhārehi. "
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, you should also remember this as an incredible and amazing quality of the Realized One. "

msgctxt "mn123:22.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, tathāgatassa viditā vedanā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti; "
msgstr "It’s that the Realized One knows feelings as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. "

msgctxt "mn123:22.3"
msgid "viditā saññā uppajjanti … pe … "
msgstr "He knows perceptions as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. "

msgctxt "mn123:22.4"
msgid "viditā vitakkā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti. "
msgstr "He knows thoughts as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. "

msgctxt "mn123:22.5"
msgid "Idampi kho tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatassa acchariyaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ dhārehī”ti. "
msgstr "This too you should remember as an incredible and amazing quality of the Realized One.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya23
msgctxt "mn123:23.1"
msgid "“Yampi, bhante, bhagavato viditā vedanā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti; "
msgstr "“Sir, the Buddha knows feelings as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. "

msgctxt "mn123:23.2"
msgid "viditā saññā … "
msgstr "He knows perceptions as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. "

msgctxt "mn123:23.3"
msgid "viditā vitakkā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti. "
msgstr "He knows thoughts as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. "

msgctxt "mn123:23.4"
msgid "Idampāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato acchariyaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ dhāremī”ti. (20) "
msgstr "This too I remember as an incredible and amazing quality of the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "mn123:23.5"
msgid "Idamavoca āyasmā ānando. "
msgstr "That’s what Ānanda said, "

msgctxt "mn123:23.6"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi; "
msgstr "and the teacher approved. "

msgctxt "mn123:23.7"
msgid "attamanā ca te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, those mendicants were happy with what Venerable Ānanda said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn123:23.8"
msgid "Acchariyaabbhutasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

